channel.title: Does this do anything?
channel.description:
If you DoS using command prompt would that even do anything these days?
1 gigabyte = 1 073 741 824 bytes...
10k bytes every second...10k * 60 = 600,000 bytes a min...36m of bytes every hour...3 hours just to waste one gig of bandwidth...(correct me if I'm wrong)
Note: I think dos dosen't do much but lag p-servers and waste bandwidth...
And basically you just flood them with your packets and ddos/dos is illegal...is that even worth it?
